com.avaya.ic.sdk

Interface Application


  • public interface Application
    The Application interface is the primary interface or starting point for any custom application that uses the IC Client SDK. You must retrieve a reference to the Application interface by calling ApplicationFactory.getApplication(). The login method of the Application interface provides a session object which is the central point for Client API usage.

      • login

        Session login(java.lang.String loginId,
              java.lang.String password,
              LoginOptions loginOptions)
       throws ConnectionException,
              AuthenticationException
        Initiates a login request into IC. After the Application instance is retrieved from the ApplicationFactory, the custom application must log in to IC. The loginId and password provided in the request must match a valid IC login specified in IC Manager.
        login() is a synchronous call. Under the hood a request is sent to the application server. The server uses the IC UOM (middleware) to log in to IC.
        To use the login() method in hoteling situations where the agent uses a different telephone than the station Id administered for that agent in IC Manager, you can pass the station Id along with the login request.
        Parameters:
        loginId - IC login ID
        password - IC login Password
        loginOptions - Optional parameters that may be passed when the custom application logs into IC.
        Returns:
        Reference to a Session if login was successful, else null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If loginId is null.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If password is null.
        ConnectionException - If a problem occurs when connecting to the server.
        AuthenticationException - If a problem occurs when authenticating the user.

      • login

        Session login(java.lang.String loginId,
              java.lang.String oldPassword,
              java.lang.String newPassword,
              LoginOptions loginOptions)
       throws ConnectionException,
              AuthenticationException
        Initiates a login request into IC and changes the current password for the agent. After the Application instance is retrieved from the ApplicationFactory, the custom application must log into IC. The loginId and password provided must be as specified in the IC Administration application.
        login() is a synchronous call. Under the hood a request is sent to the application server. The server uses the IC UOM (middleware) to log in to IC.
        To use the login() method in hoteling situations where the agent uses a different telephone than the station Id administered for that agent in IC Manager, you can pass the station Id along with the login request.
        Parameters:
        loginId - IC login ID
        oldPassword - IC login Current Password
        newPassword - IC login New Password
        loginOptions - Optional parameters that may be passed while logging into IC.
        Returns:
        Reference to a Session if login was successful, else null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If loginId is null.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If password is null.
        ConnectionException - If a problem occurs when connecting to the server.
        AuthenticationException - If a problem occurs when authenticating the user.

      • logout

        void logout(java.lang.String loginId,
            ReasonCode reasonCode)
        Logs out the specified agent from the IC system. The Session is invalidated at this point. Ensure that the WorkList does not contain WorkItems with active MediaInteractions when attempting logout.
        Parameters:
        loginId - IC login ID
        reasonCode - The logout reason code to use.
